      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openrouter,discord,google): bound OAuth/gateway response body reads",
        "body": "Bound three unbounded response body reads to prevent potential OOM across bundled plugins.\n\n### Changes\n\n1. **extensions/openrouter/oauth.ts** — The success path in `readResponseBody` used unbounded `await response.text()` while the error path already used `readResponseTextLimited`. Added `OPENROUTER_OAUTH_RESPONSE_BODY_LIMIT_BYTES` (16 KiB) for the OK path.\n\n2. **extensions/google/oauth.token.ts** — Both the error text extraction and the JSON response in `requestTokenGrant` were unbounded. Replaced with `readResponseTextLimited(response, 4 KiB)` for error text and `readProviderJsonResponse` for the success JSON body.\n\n3. **extensions/discord/src/monitor/gateway-metadata.ts** — `fetchDiscordGatewayInfo` read the entire gateway bot info response via unbounded `await response.text()`. Replaced with `readResponseTextLimited(response, 16 KiB)`.\n\n### Context\n\nThis follows the same project-wide bound-response-read pattern as recent fixes like #97702, #88401, #97615, #97281, and others.\n\n### Verification\n\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/openrouter` — 10 files, 113 tests passed\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/google/oauth.test.ts` — 1 file, 27 tests passed\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/google/oauth.http.test.ts` — passed\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/discord` — 161 files, 1809 tests passed\n- ✅ `pnpm tsgo:extensions` — clean\n\n### AI-Assisted\n\nThis PR was AI-assisted.",
